The energy of the photon is: \[ E = \frac{hc}{\lambda} = \frac{(6.626 \times 10^{-34} \, \text{J·s})(3.00 \times 10^8 \, \text{m/s})}{4.28 \times 10^{-7} \, \text{m}} = 4.6178 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J} \] This energy is entirely converted into the kinetic energy of the electron, given by \( KE = \frac{1}{2}mv^2 \). Solving for the velocity \( v \): \[ v = \sqrt{\frac{2E}{m}} = \sqrt{\frac{2 \times 4.6178 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J}}{9.109 \times 10^{-31} \, \text{kg}}} \] Calculating the numerator and denominator: \[ \text{Numerator: } 2 \times 4.6178 \times 10^{-19} = 9.2356 \times 10^{-19} \, \text{J} \] \[ \text{Denominator: } 9.109 \times 10^{-31} \, \text{kg} \] \[ \frac{9.2356 \times 10^{-19}}{9.109 \times 10^{-31}} = 1.0138 \times 10^{12} \] Taking the square root: \[ v = \sqrt{1.0138 \times 10^{12}} \approx 1.0068 \times 10^6 \, \text{m/s} \] Rounding to two decimal places, the velocity of the electron is: \[ \boxed{1.01 \times 10^6} \, \text{m/s} \]
